6: Whoa... This is the World Flipper?!
9:
A portal into other worlds, huh?
Heh. What an exciting thing to be 
hiding in one's basement.
12:
Now, why don't you gentle folk show 
me how the magic happens?
16:
Why don't we talk about how you sold 
us out first?
20:
Enough, Nimbus. All's well that ends 
well.
So... we have found our fifth World 
Flipper.
28:
Searching for coordinates.
Light, your world is—
35:
Starview Village... Why are we being 
shown this?
40:
I am Lux. I come in answer to your 
summons.
41:
Tell me, Oracle. Why call me here to 
this world, when all the fiends have 
already been banished?
45:
Welcome to Starview Village. I am... 
of... stars...
59:
I had a dream... A vision.
Stella, you were there too. Tell me what 
you saw.
62:
A champion arrived at Starview 
Village... to have an audience with the 
Oracle...
67:
I recognized his name... Legends sing 
of Lux—of how he single-handedly 
toppled the Dark Throne.
69:
But he lived long ago... During an age 
unnamed and all but lost...
73:
Who was the Oracle? What connection 
did she bear... to me?
79:
I have no idea what's going on, but 
I can say one thing! You'll work 
through it, Stella! I KNOW you will!
82:
It might have been a memory. Of the 
village itself.
86:
It's not rare, you know—for forgotten 
memories to come bubbling back to 
the surface. Data's harder to erase 
than you'd think.
87:
And when you're searching for these 
coordinates, you're sifting through 
data, right? I can imagine some extra 
chaff being caught up in the sieve.
92: Thank you. I'm all right now.
96:
And, for all my doubts, I do know one 
thing. I am an oracle to champions.
100: Yes... Yes, I believe you're right.
104:
Let us keep collecting coordinates. 
Something tells me they'll be 
important.
112:
But before that, food... The room's 
startin' to spin...
117:
Heh. Dinner'll be on the stove the 
second we get back to Starview.
120:
Food... *sigh* I would've liked to ingest 
organic matter...
123: Dia... Are you not coming with us?
128:
I mean, I was planning to. But I figured 
I'd better stay and help Regis get all 
those lost memories back to their 
owners.
130:
My music should make the process 
a little easier.
But as soon as that's done... it's hello 
Starview!
138:
Hehe. I'll probably have written a few 
new songs by then.
146:
Me... sing? That may be outside the 
realm of possibility.
149:
Oh, please! Nothing's impossible!
You guys proved that to me.
151:
We're singing together, Stella! And 
that's that!
160: Cross your heart and hope to die.
164:
Come on, Stella. We'll meet again 
soon.
